modules.description: Performs VLQ (Variable-Length Quantity) encoding and decoding on integers, using Base64 representation. Encodes integers into a Base64 VLQ string in a buffer and decodes a Base64 VLQ stream into integers. Used for efficiently storing or transmitting variable-length integer values, such as in source map generation or binary compression formats.

Encodes and decodes integers using Base64 VLQ (Variable-Length Quantity) encoding. Operates on integers and byte buffers, producing compact string representations suitable for source maps or binary compression. Directly handles variable-length integer serialization for efficient storage or transmission.
